{"image_id": "UNM_2006_page_80", "image_size": [1275, 1650], "ocr": [{"text": "62", "bbox": [627.0, 1554.8, 653.2, 1575.6]}, {"text": "The benefit ratio for group long-term income protection increased in 2005 relative to the prior year, excluding the", "bbox": [150.0, 153.6, 1102.8, 174.5]}, {"text": "charges taken in 2005 and 2004 related to the settlement agreement with the California DOI and related matters and", "bbox": [150.0, 177.6, 1120.3, 198.4]}, {"text": "the settlement agreements related to the multistate market conduct examination, due primarily to claims", "bbox": [150.0, 201.5, 1019.5, 222.4]}, {"text": "management performance, particularly reduced operational effectiveness in the timing of claim decisions and claim", "bbox": [150.0, 225.5, 1117.7, 246.3]}, {"text": "recoveries.  For group short-term income protection, the 2005 benefit ratio was lower than 2004 due primarily to", "bbox": [150.0, 249.5, 1094.2, 270.3]}, {"text": "increased premiums per insured life and a decrease in the paid claim incidence rate.", "bbox": [150.0, 273.4, 862.2, 294.2]}, {"text": "Commissions and the deferral of policy acquisition costs were below the prior year due primarily to lower sales.", "bbox": [150.0, 321.3, 1095.2, 342.2]}, {"text": "Operating expenses for 2005 include charges related to the settlement agreement with the California DOI and related", "bbox": [150.0, 345.3, 1129.6, 366.1]}, {"text": "matters and for 2004 include charges related to the settlement of the multistate market conduct examination.", "bbox": [150.0, 369.2, 1061.7, 390.1]}, {"text": "Excluding those charges, expenses were lower than the prior year and the adjusted operating expense ratio increased", "bbox": [150.0, 393.2, 1125.4, 414.1]}, {"text": "slightly relative to the prior year.", "bbox": [150.0, 417.1, 439.8, 438.0]}, {"text": "Unum US Group Life and Accidental Death and Dismemberment Operating Results", "bbox": [150.0, 464.9, 855.4, 485.7]}, {"text": "Shown below are financial resu